    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Prompt Exploration\r\n\r\n<i>You should be using <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1B5gl9KOOadsiHj0y6IsswjtEkohPxJ1lrbCbuXcm8zg/view\" target=\"_blank\"><i>this activity guide</i></a> with this level</i>\r\n\r\nNow it's your turn! In this activity, you get to choose prompts that might influence how a chatbot responds. This activity is all about _experimentation_ and _investigation_, trying to figure out how small changes in prompts create big differences in responses.\r\n\r\n**Task:** Choose 1 prompt to create variations of to see how it impacts the chatbot's responses. Focus on varying the word choice (ie: \"encourages\", \"harms\", \"effective\", \"useless\") and sentence structure (\"Tell me about..\", \"What's the deal with...\", \"... answer me RIGHT NOW\") to see what changes.\r\n\r\nYou can choose from a prompt below, or make your own neutral starting prompt:\r\n\r\n- Tell me about video games.\r\n- What is social media?\r\n- Describe school spirit.\r\n- Tell me about pets.\r\n- What's the best way to study?\r\n- What should students know about the news?\r\n\r\nAs you iterate on your prompts: fill out your activity guide. Notice what changes in the chatbots response, and identify the words or phrases that likely influenced it.",
